No active project context. Call `{{tool_prefix}}set_project` with the repository root before proceeding.

Determine the repository root: run `git rev-parse --git-common-dir`. If it returns `.git`, the repository root is the current working directory. Otherwise, resolve the result to an absolute path and, if it names a `.git` directory, use its parent directory as the repository root. Fall back to CWD if not a git repository.
Never pass the `.git` directory itself to `{{tool_prefix}}set_project`.
All relative paths used by the MCP server are interpreted relative to the project root you provide to `set_project`.
{{#agent.is_claude}}
Note: AI agents may run inside a linked worktree — `git rev-parse --git-common-dir` returns the main repository's `.git`, not the worktree's.
{{/agent.is_claude}}
